Definition: from {{h5674}}; a crossing-place; ferry, plain (from the margin).
feminine of {{h5676}}; an outburst of passion; anger, rage, wrath.
from {{h5670}}; something pledged, i.e. (collectively) pawned goods; thick clay (by a false etym.).
a primitive root; to pawn; causatively, to lend (on security); figuratively, to entangle; borrow, break (ranks), fetch (a pledge), lend, × surely.
(Aramaic) from {{h5648}}; labor or business; affairs, service, work.
or עֳבִי]; from {{h5666}}; density, i.e. depth or width; thick(-ness). Compare {{h5645}}.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5676}}; beyond, this side.

a primitive root; to cross over; used very widely of any transition (literal or figurative; transitive, intransitive, intensive, causative); specifically, to cover (in copulation); alienate, alter, × at all, beyond, bring (over, through), carry over, (over-) come (on, over), conduct (over), convey over, current, deliver, do away, enter, escape, fail, gender, get over, (make) go (away, beyond, by, forth, his way, in, on, over, through), have away (more), lay, meddle, overrun, make partition, (cause to, give, make to, over) pass(-age, along, away, beyond, by, -enger, on, out, over, through), (cause to, make)   proclaim(-amation), perish, provoke to anger, put away, rage,   raiser of taxes, remove, send over, set apart,   shave, cause to (make) sound, × speedily, × sweet smelling, take (away), (make to) transgress(-or), translate, turn away, (way-) faring man, be wrath.
the same as {{h5676}}; Eber, the name of two patriarchs and four Israelites; Eber, Heber.

from {{h5674}}; properly, a region across; but used only adverbially (with or without a preposition) on the opposite side (especially of the Jordan; ususally meaning the east); × against, beyond, by, × from, over, passage, quarter, (other, this) side, straight.
or עָבֻר; passive participle of {{h5674}}; properly, crossed, i.e. (abstractly) transit; used only adverbially, on account of, in order that; because of, for (...'s sake), (intent) that, to.
the same as {{h5668}}; passed, i.e. kept over; used only of stored grain; old corn.
from {{h5695}}; vituline; Eglon, the name of a place in Palestine and of a Moabitish king; Eglon.
or עֹבַדְיָהוּ; active participle of {{h5647}} and {{h3050}}; serving Jah; Obadjah, the name of thirteen Israelites; Obadiah.
from {{h5650}} and {{h4428}}; servant of a king; Ebed-Melek, a eunuch of Zedekeah; Ebed-melech.
from {{h5647}}; serviceable; Abdi, the name of two Israelites; Abdi.
from {{h5650}} and {{h410}}; servant of God; Abdiel, an Israelite; Abdiel. Compare {{h5655}}.
a primitive root; to be dense; be (grow) thick(-er).
or עֲבֹט; from {{h5670}}; a pawn; pledge.
the same as {{h5665}}; Abed-Nego, the Babylonian name of one of Daniel's companions; Abed-nego.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; Abed-Nego, the name of Azariah; Abed-nego.
passive participle of {{h5647}}; something wrought, i.e. (concretely) service; household, store of servants.
or עֲבוֹדָה; from {{h5647}}; work of any kind; act, bondage,   bondservant, effect, labour, ministering(-try), office, service(-ile, -itude), tillage, use, work, × wrought.
from {{h5647}} and {{h410}}; serving God; Abdeel, an Israelite; Abdeel. Compare {{h5661}}.
from the active participle of {{h5647}} and {{h123}}; worker of Edom; Obed-Edom, the name of five Israelites; Obed-edom.
from {{h5647}}; work; Abda, the name of two Israelites; Abda
from {{h5647}}; a deed; work.
the same as {{h5650}}; Ebed, the name of two Israelites; Ebed.
from {{h5647}}; a servant; × bondage, bondman, (bond-) servant, (man-) servant.
from {{h5647}}; servitude; bondage.
from {{h5647}}; servitude; Abdon, the name of a place in Palestine and of four Israelites; Abdon. Compare {{h5683}}.
or שָׂתַם; (Numbers 24:15), a primitive root; to stop up; by implication, to repair; figuratively, to keep secret; closed up, hidden, secret, shut out (up), stop.
a primitive root; to hide (by covering), literally or figuratively; be absent, keep close, conceal, hide (self), (keep) secret, × surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5641}}; to conceal; figuratively, to demolish; destroy, secret thing.

or (feminine) סִתְרָה; (Deuteronomy 32:38), from {{h5641}}; a cover (in a good or a bad, a literal or a figurative sense); backbiting, covering, covert, × disguise(-th), hiding place, privily, protection, secret(-ly, place).
from {{h5643}}; protective; Sithri, an Israelite,; Zithri.

(masculine and feminine); from {{h5743}}; properly, an envelope, i.e. darkness (or density, 2 Chronicles 4:17); specifically, a (scud) cloud; also a copse; clay, (thick) cloud, × thick, thicket. Compare {{h5672}}.
or עֹב; from an unused root meaning to cover; properly, equivalent to {{h5645}}; but used only as an architectural term,; an architrave (as shading the pillars); thick (beam, plant).

a primitive root; to work (in any sense); by implication, to serve, till, (causatively) enslave, etc.; × be, keep in bondage, be bondmen, bond-service, compel, do, dress, ear, execute,   husbandman, keep, labour(-ing man, bring to pass, (cause to, make to) serve(-ing, self), (be, become) servant(-s), do (use) service, till(-er), transgress (from margin), (set a) work, be wrought, worshipper,
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h5647}}; to do, make, prepare, keep, etc.; × cut, do, execute, go on, make, move, work.
(Aramaic) from {{h5648}}; a servant; servant.
a primitive root; to cremate, i.e. to be (near) of kin (such being privileged to kindle the pyre); burn.
for {{h5589}}; a twig; bough.
a primitive root; to turn away, i.e. (morally) be refractory; × away, backsliding, rebellious, revolter(-ing), slide back, stubborn, withdrew.
from {{h5635}}; a nettle (as stinging like a burn); brier.

or סָרִס; from an unused root meaning to castrate; a eunuch; by implication, valet (especially of the female apartments), and thus, a minister of state; chamberlain, eunuch, officer. Compare {{h7249}}.
for {{h8302}}; a coat of mail; brigandine.
from an unused root of uncertain meaning; an axle; figuratively, a peer; lord, plate.
(Aramaic) of foreign origin; an emir; president.
from {{h5641}}; hidden; Sethur, an Israelite; Sethur.
from an unused root meaning to hide; winter (as the dark season); winter.
from {{h5493}}; departure; Sirah, a cistern so-called; Sirah. See also {{h5518}}.
from {{h5493}}; apostasy, crime; figuratively, remission; × continual, rebellion, revolt(-ed), turn away, wrong.
from a primitive root meaning to tremble; trembling; Sered, an Israelite; Sered.
patron from {{h5624}}; a Seredite (collectively) or descendants of Sered; Sardites.
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a cloak; coat.
of foreign derivation; Sargon, an Assyrian king; Sargon.
contracted from {{h5637}}; peevish; heavy, sad.
from an unused root meaning to sting; a thistle; brier.
a primitive root; to extend (even to excess); exceeding, hand, spread, stretch self, banish.
from {{h5628}}; a redundancy; remnant.
from the same as {{h5696}}; something revolving, i.e. a wheeled vehicle; cart, chariot, wagon
the same as {{h5697}}; Eglah, a wife of David; Eglah.
passive part (but with active sense) of an unused root meaning to twitter; probably the swallow; swallow.
from {{h5746}}; an ashcake (as round); cake (upon the hearth).
from {{h5689}}; love (abstractly), i.e. amorousness; inordinate love.
from {{h5689}}; love (concretely), i.e. amative words; much love, very lovely.
feminine of {{h5695}}; a (female) calf, especially one nearly grown (i.e. a heifer); calf, cow, heifer.
or עָגוֹל; from an unused root meaning to revolve,; circular; round.
from the same as {{h5696}}; a (male) calf (as frisking round), especially one nearly grown (i.e. a steer); bullock, calf.
from the same as {{h5696}}; something round, i.e. a ring (for the ears); earring.
(Aramaic) from the same as {{h5609}}; a scribe (secular or sacred); scribe.
or (feminine) סִפְרָה; (Psalm 56:8 ({{h9}})), from {{h5608}}; properly, writing (the art or a document); by implication, a book; bill, book, evidence, × learn(-ed) (-ing), letter, register, scroll.
the same as {{h5610}}; Sephar, a place in Arabia; Sephar.
from {{h5608}}; a census; numbering.
(dual); or סְפָרִים; of foreign derivation; Sepharvajim or Sepharim; Sepharvaim.
patrial from {{h5617}}; a Sepharvite or inhabitant of Sepharvain; Sepharvite.
from {{h5608}}; a numeration; number.
of foreign derivation; Sepharad, a region of Assyria; Sepharad.
a primitive root; properly, to be weighty; but used only in the sense of lapidation or its contrary (as if a delapidation); (cast, gather out, throw) stone(-s), × surely.
feminine active participle of {{h5608}}; a scribe (properly, female); Sophereth, a temple servant; Sophereth.
feminine of {{h5683}}; Ebronah, place in the Desert; Ebronah.
a primitive root; to dry up; be rotten.
a primitive root; to interlace, i.e. (figuratively) to pervert; wrap up.
or עָבוֹת; from {{h5686}}; intwined, i.e. dense; thick.
patronymic from {{h5677}}; an Eberite (i.e. Hebrew) or descendant of Eber; Hebrew(-ess, woman).
the same as {{h5680}}; Ibri, an Israelite; Ibri.
plural of {{h5676}}; regions beyond; Abarim, a place in Palestine; Abarim, passages.
from {{h5676}}; transitional; Ebron, a place in Palestine; Hebron. Perhaps a clerical error for {{h5658}}.
or עֲבוֹת; or (feminine) עֲבֹתָה; the same as {{h5687}}; something intwined, i.e. a string, wreath or foliage; band, cord, rope, thick bough (branch), wreathen (chain).
a primitive root; to breathe after, i.e. to love (sensually); dote, lover.

a primitive root; properly, to score with a mark as a tally or record, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe, and also to enumerate; intensively, to recount, i.e. celebrate; commune, (ac-) count; declare, number,   penknife, reckon, scribe, shew forth, speak, talk, tell (out), writer.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h5608}}; a book; book, roll.
from {{h5603}}; a wainscot; ceiling.
a primitive root; properly, to snatch away, i.e. terminate; but used only as denominative from {{h5592}} (in the sense of a vestibule),; to wait at the threshold; be a doorkeeper.

or שָׂפַק; (1 Kings 20:10; Job 27:23; Isaiah 2:6), a primitive root; to clap the hands (in token of compact, derision, grief, indignation, or punishment); by implication of satisfaction, to be enough; by implication of excess, to vomit; clap, smite, strike, suffice, wallow.
or שֶׂפֶק; (Job 20:22; Job 36:18), from {{h5606}}; chastisement; also satiety; stroke, sufficiency.
from {{h5608}}; a gem (perhaps used for scratching other substances), probably the sapphire; sapphire.
from an unused root meaning to depress; a basin (as deepened out); bowl, dish.
a primitive root; to hide by covering; specifically, to roof (passive participle as noun, a roof) or wainscot; figuratively, to reserve; cieled, cover, seated.
